  "text": "Curable hepatocellular carcinoma (HCC) is gradually increasing because of improved follow-up and imaging diagnosis protocols for chronic liver diseases. However, a therapeutic strategy for metastasis and recurrence of HCC remains a difficult topic. Recurrent HCC in the extrahepatic bile duct is somewhat rare, and almost all cases are diagnosed after the manifestation of sudden obstructive jaundice [CITATION_1] . We report a case of recurrent HCC in the common bile duct due to hematogenous metastasis with tumor thrombus 50 months after primary hepatectomy.",
